3.16 XPath I: Selecting Elements


mypage.html

&lt;div class="container"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Header&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p id="page-content"&gt;Content&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;img class="footer-image m-5" src="footer.png"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


'//div' matches all elements &lt;div&gt; in the document:
&lt;div class="container"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Header&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p id="page-content"&gt;Content&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;img class="footer-image m-5" src="footer.png"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;
'//div//img' matches &lt;img&gt; elements which are children of &lt;div&gt; elements:
&lt;img class="footer-image m-5" src="footer.png"&gt;

3.17 XPath II: Filtering by Attributes


mypage.html

&lt;div class="container"&gt;
  &lt;h1&gt;Header&lt;/h1&gt;
  &lt;p id="page-content"&gt;Content&lt;/p&gt;
  &lt;img class="footer-image m-5" src="footer.png"&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;


'//p[id="page-content"]' matches all &lt;p&gt; elements with id page-content2:
&lt;p id="page-content"&gt;Content&lt;/p&gt;
Matching classes is a bit trickier:
'//img[contains(concat(" ", normalize-space(@class), " "), " footer-image ")]'
matches all &lt;img&gt; elements with page-content as one of their classes3
&lt;img class="footer-image m-5" src="footer.png"&gt;

3.19 Authentication via GH

The GH library for R can handle this authentication process for you. For example, this private repo in my account does not show up if requested anonymously, but does show up when requested using GH with a Personal Access Token4:



Code
library(gh)
# We use tryCatch so that code still runs even if (a) GITHUB_TOKEN isn't set, or (b) no internet connection
success &lt;- FALSE
result &lt;- tryCatch( 
  {
    gh("GET /repos/jpowerj/private-repo-test")
    success &lt;- TRUE
  },
  error = function(e) {
    success &lt;- FALSE
    writeLines("Could not fetch github repo")
  }
)


